# Niagara System: Dinosaur Presence Effects
# Enhances the feeling that dinosaurs are living, breathing creatures

## EMITTER 1: Breathing Steam (Large Predators)
- Spawn Rate: 15-25 particles/second (tied to breathing animation)
- Lifetime: 3-6 seconds
- Size: 1.0-3.0 world units
- Velocity: Forward from nostrils, slight upward curve
- Color: White-gray (240,240,240) fading to transparent
- Material: M_Steam_Volumetric

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Nostril bone sockets
- Velocity: Animation-driven direction + random spread
- Size Over Life: Rapid expansion then fade
- Temperature Influence: More visible in cold weather
- Wind Interaction: Disperses with environmental wind

### Animation Integration:
- Breathing_Rate_Parameter: Links to creature AI state
- Exertion_Multiplier: Increases during chase/combat
- Temperature_Modifier: Weather system integration

## EMITTER 2: Footstep Dust Clouds
- Spawn Rate: Burst on footfall events (50-100 particles)
- Lifetime: 2-4 seconds
- Size: 0.5-2.0 world units
- Velocity: Outward from impact point
- Color: Ground material dependent (brown/gray/green)
- Material: M_Dust_Ground

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Foot bone impact position
- Velocity: Radial burst with ground normal influence
- Ground Material Detection: Surface type affects color/amount
- Creature Weight Scaling: Larger dinosaurs = bigger clouds
- Collision: Ground settle with bounce damping

### Surface Response System:
- Mud: Dark brown, sticky particles, longer lifetime
- Dry Earth: Light brown, quick dispersion
- Grass: Green tint, mixed with grass fragments
- Rock: Gray particles, spark effects on hard impact

## EMITTER 3: Eye Reflection Glints
- Spawn Rate: 2-5 particles/second
- Lifetime: 0.5-1.5 seconds
- Size: 0.1-0.3 world units
- Velocity: Minimal, follows eye movement
- Color: Bright white-blue (255,255,255)
- Material: M_EyeGlint_Additive

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Eye bone sockets
- Camera Angle Dependency: Only visible at certain viewing angles
- Blink Integration: Disappears during blink animations
- Intelligence Indicator: Frequency varies by species intelligence
- Distance Culling: Not visible beyond 30 meters

## EMITTER 4: Saliva Drips (Predators Only)
- Spawn Rate: 1-3 particles/second
- Lifetime: 2-5 seconds
- Size: 0.2-0.5 world units
- Velocity: Gravity-driven downward
- Color: Clear with slight yellow tint (255,255,200,180)
- Material: M_Saliva_Translucent

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Mouth/jaw bone positions
- Gravity: Strong downward pull
- Collision: Ground splatter effect
- Hunger State: More frequent when hunting
- Stress Response: Increases during combat

## SYSTEM PARAMETERS (Per Creature Type):
- Creature_Size_Scale: 0.5-3.0 (affects all effect scales)
- Activity_Level: 0.0-2.0 (calm to aggressive states)
- Health_State: 0.0-1.0 (affects breathing intensity)
- Environmental_Adaptation: Species-specific modifiers